     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <head>The Booke to the Reader.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>LOk<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>
         <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="2 letters">
            <desc>••</desc>
         </gap> thou leape, dome not by viewe of face</l>
      <l>Least hast make wast, in myssedoming the case▪</l>
      <l>For I teac<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap> n<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="2 letters">
            <desc>••</desc>
         </gap> to Loue, ne yet his lore,</l>
      <l>Ne with what s<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>lue is cured such a sore:</l>
      <l>But I the carke with <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>ares that thereby happs,</l>
      <l>The blysse with ioyes, the storms with thunder clapps,</l>
      <l>The curtesies, where most his force is shewde,</l>
      <l>The choise of best, be it of good or <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="3 letters">
            <desc>•••</desc>
         </gap>de,</l>
      <l>Compare them so, as domed is the doubt</l>
      <l>Thereof, and aye the truth well sifted ou<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>▪</l>
      <l>The which to reade such pleasure thou shalt finde</l>
      <l>As may content a well dysposed minde.</l>
   </lg>
</div>
